        parsed_args={
            'prompt': 'What does the filing disclose about the common-control accounting recast, including the merger of xAI and X Holdings, and how historical periods are presented? Please describe the retrospective recast and its impact on comparability. {{spacex_s1}}'
        }
    ),
    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# Common-Control Accounting Recast: xAI and X Holdings Merger\n\n## Merger Timeline\n\nThe filing discloses two sequential share-exchange transactions, collectively referred to as the "Mergers":\n\n1. **X Merger (March 28, 2025):** xAI completed its acquisition of X Holdings Corp. ("X") and X.AI Corp., making them wholly-owned subsidiaries of xAI. X Holdings is the parent of the platform formerly known as Twitter (acquired by Elon Musk in October 2022), while X.AI Corp. began operations in March 2023.\n\n2. **xAI Merger (February 2, 2026):** SpaceX completed its acquisition of X.AI Holdings Corp. ("xAI"), making xAI a wholly-owned subsidiary of SpaceX.\n\n## Common-Control Rationale\n\nBoth Mergers were accounted for as **reorganizations of entities under common control** because Elon Musk held a controlling financial interest in SpaceX, xAI, and X through his majority voting interest in each entity during all periods presented. This determination is critical because it dictates the accounting method: rather than purchase accounting (which would require fair-value step-ups and goodwill recognition), common-control accounting permits—or requires—retrospective combination at historical carrying amounts.\n\n## Retrospective Recast—Mechanics and Scope\n\nThe consolidated financial statements have been **retrospectively recast for all periods presented** to include:\n\n- The historical results of X.AI Holdings Corp. (acquired by SpaceX effective February 2, 2026), and\n- X Holdings Corp. (acquired by xAI effective March 28, 2025),\n\nbecause these transactions were between entities under common control. The specific mechanics include:\n\n### Net Assets and Operations\n- The net assets of SpaceX, xAI, and X are combined at their **historical carrying amounts** for all periods presented.\n- **No new goodwill or other intangible assets** were recorded as a result of either Merger.\n- All **historical related-party transactions** between the entities have been **eliminated in consolidation**.\n\n### Capital Stock and Shareholders\' Equity\n- Capital stock and shareholders\' equity reflect a **continuation of historical SpaceX capital stock and shareholders\' equity**, combined with the historical capital stock and shareholders\' equity of X and xAI, as adjusted by the respective exchange ratios used to effect the Mergers.\n- All shares of historical X, X.AI Corp., and xAI Common Stock are presented in the financial statements **as if converted into SpaceX Common Stock at the applicable exchange rate** for all periods presented through the xAI Merger Date.\n\n### Exchange Ratios Applied Retrospectively\n\n| Transaction | Security Converted | Into | Ratio |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| X Merger | X Common Stock (each class) | xAI Common Stock (same class) | 2.776:1 |\n| X Merger | X.AI Corp. Common Stock | xAI Common Stock (same class) | 1.000:1 |\n| X Merger | X.AI Corp. Preferred Stock | xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock | 1.000:1 |\n| xAI Merger | xAI Common Stock (Class A, B, Limited Voting) | SpaceX Common Stock | 0.1433:1 |\n| xAI Merger | xAI Series A-1, B, C, D, E Preferred ("Low Vote") | SpaceX Class A Common Stock | 0.1433:1 |\n| xAI Merger | xAI Series A Preferred ("High Vote") | SpaceX Class B Common Stock | 0.1433:1 |\n\n(All ratios are on a pre-2026 Stock Split basis.)\n\n### Exception: xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock\n\nA significant exception to the retrospective recast involves xAI\'s Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock:\n\n- Because this stock was **legally outstanding during all historical periods** prior to the xAI Merger and represented a **separate equity class of a legally distinct predecessor entity**, its conversion into SpaceX Common Stock is recognized **only as of the closing of the xAI Merger (February 2, 2026), and not retrospectively**.\n- Historical consolidated balance sheets and statements of redeemable convertible preferred stock and shareholders\' equity reflect the xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock as **outstanding xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock**, consistent with its legal form and rights during those periods.\n- The balances are **not recast on an as-converted basis** for periods prior to the xAI Merger Date.\n- The impact of the conversion is presented **separately** in the consolidated statements of redeemable convertible preferred stock and shareholders\' equity for the three months ended March 31, 2026.\n- xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock is classified **outside of permanent equity** as "Redeemable convertible preferred stock" on the consolidated balance sheets and has not been remeasured to its redemption amount because the shares are not currently redeemable.\n\n### Customer Warrants\nxAI had issued warrants to customers with a ten-year term (originally expiring 2035), an exercise price equal to par value, and vesting tied to payments received. The closing of the xAI Merger triggered an acceleration clause causing all outstanding warrants (vested and unvested) to be **automatically exercised on a cashless basis** and converted into fully vested SpaceX Class A Common Stock at the 0.1433 exchange ratio.\n\n## 2026 Stock Split\n\nOn May 4, 2026, SpaceX effected a **five-for-one forward stock split** of its authorized, issued, and outstanding shares of Class A, Class B, and Class C Common Stock. The conversion rate of SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was proportionately adjusted. All share and per share information throughout the prospectus has been **retroactively adjusted** to reflect the 2026 Stock Split for all periods presented.\n\n## Change in Reporting Entity\n\nThe filing explicitly states that this presentation **constitutes a change in reporting entity**. As a consequence:\n\n- **Separate financial statements of xAI and X are not provided**, because the consolidated financial statements already reflect the reorganization of entities under common control for all periods presented.\n- The summary historical consolidated financial and operating data is presented on a combined basis and is **not indicative of results to be expected for any future period**, and interim period results are not necessarily indicative of full fiscal period results.\n\n## Impact on Comparability\n\nThe retrospective recast has several important implications for comparability:\n\n1. **All historical periods now include xAI and X results.** Any period presented in the financial statements—whether before or after the actual merger dates—reflects the combined operations of SpaceX, xAI, and X. This means that revenue, expenses, assets, and liabilities for prior periods are materially different from what SpaceX previously reported on a standalone basis.\n\n2. **No purchase-price allocation effects.** Because no goodwill or intangible assets were recorded, there are no amortization charges or impairment risks arising from the Mergers themselves. However, this also means the balance sheet does not reflect any fair-value step-up for xAI\'s or X\'s assets, which investors might expect in a traditional business combination.\n\n3. **Intercompany eliminations affect historical relationships.** Because all historical related-party transactions between SpaceX, xAI, and X have been eliminated, revenue or cost figures that previously included intercompany dealings are now presented on a consolidated basis, potentially altering apparent growth rates or margin profiles.\n\n4. **Equity structure complexity.** The capital stock presentation combines three historically separate equity structures at different exchange ratios, with the xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock treated on a non-recast basis until the xAI Merger Date. This creates a discontinuity in the equity presentation at February 2, 2026, when the preferred stock converts and the share counts jump (e.g., Class A shares increased from 1,952 million at December 31, 2025, to 2,884 million at March 31, 2026, with 886 million shares issued upon conversion of redeemable convertible preferred stock pursuant to the xAI Merger).\n\n5. **Per-share metrics are affected by the 2026 Stock Split.** All per-share data has been retroactively adjusted by a factor of five, meaning historical per-share figures differ from any previously reported amounts by that factor.\n\n6. **Cross-period comparisons require care.** Because the X Merger occurred on March 28, 2025, and the xAI Merger on February 2, 2026, periods that straddle these dates include partial-year contributions from the acquired entities on a retrospective basis, but the legal and operational integration effects (such as synergies, restructuring, or changes in business strategy) would only manifest prospectively.\n\nIn summary, the filing presents a fully recast set of financial statements in which SpaceX, xAI, and X are treated as a single economic entity for all periods presented, with historical carrying amounts preserved, intercompany transactions eliminated, and equity structures combined at specified exchange ratios—subject to the notable exception that xAI\'s Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock is not recast to an as-converted basis prior to the xAI Merger Date. This approach enhances period-over-period comparability within the recast statements but means the figures are not comparable to any previously reported standalone SpaceX financials.',
