    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='## Cautionary Language on Comparability of Recast Financial Statements\n\n### Not Indicative of Future Results\n\nYes, the filing explicitly states that the combined results are not indicative of future results. The specific language reads:\n\n> "The summary historical consolidated financial and operating data presented below is **not indicative of the results to be expected for any future period**, and the results for any interim period are **not necessarily indicative of the results to be expected for the full fiscal period**."\n\nThis cautionary statement appears twice in the preamble — once in the Summary Historical Consolidated Financial and Operating Data section and again in the contiguous block extension — underscoring its emphasis.\n\n### Change in Reporting Entity\n\nThe filing explains the retrospective combination as follows:\n\n> "The summary historical consolidated financial and operating data of SpaceX has been prepared to reflect the **retrospective combination of the companies for all periods presented** to include the historical results of **xAI**, which was acquired by SpaceX, effective **February 2, 2026**, and **X Holdings**, which was acquired by xAI, effective **March 28, 2025**, because these transactions were between **entities under common control**."\n\nElsewhere in the financial statement notes, the filing explicitly labels this as a change in reporting entity:\n\n> "This presentation constitutes a **change in reporting entity**."\n\nIt further notes that because the consolidated financial statements already reflect the reorganization for all periods presented, **separate financial statements of xAI and X are not provided**.\n\n### Interim Period Results\n\nThe cautionary language on interim results appears in two places:\n\n1. **In the summary preamble**: "the results for any interim period are not necessarily indicative of the results to be expected for the full fiscal period."\n\n2. **In Note 2 (Summary of Significant Accounting Policies)**, applying to the unaudited interim financials: "The consolidated results of operations for any interim period are **not necessarily indicative of the results to be expected for the full year or for any other future years or interim periods**."\n\n### Direction to MD&A\n\nThe filing directs readers to the MD&A and full financial statements:\n\n> "The following information should be read together with **\'Management\'s Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operations\'** and our consolidated financial statements and related notes thereto included elsewhere in this prospectus. The summary historical consolidated financial data included in this section is **not intended to replace** the consolidated financial statements and is **qualified in its entirety** by our consolidated financial statements and related notes included elsewhere in this prospectus."\n\n### Summary\n\n| Cautionary Element | Language Used |\n|---|---|\n| Future results | "Not indicative of the results to be expected for any future period" |\n| Interim periods | "Not necessarily indicative of the results to be expected for the full fiscal period" / "full year or for any other future years or interim periods" |\n| Change in reporting entity | Retrospective combination of xAI (acquired Feb 2, 2026) and X Holdings (acquired Mar 28, 2025) under common control; "This presentation constitutes a change in reporting entity" |\n| Reader direction | Read together with MD&A and full consolidated financial statements; summary data is "qualified in its entirety" by the full financials |',
